{"type": "article", "id": 29826, "title": "磁铁相吸的吊灯", "description": "", "date": "2016-07-19T23:03:56Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [], "category": 25, "column": 28, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 0, "praise_count": 34, "image": "img/article/article_show/2016071917182626dExGJDS0PKynhM.jpg", "contents": "<p>          </p><p>意大利设计师 <a href=\"http://vittoriovenezia.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Vittorio Venezia</a> 和 <a href=\"http://www.andreasignoretto.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Andrea Signoretto</a> 为 <a href=\"http://www.luce5.it/en/\" rel=\"nofollow\">LUCE5</a> 设计的吊灯 <a href=\"http://vittoriovenezia.com/#/magnetica/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Magnetica</a> 吸引的不只是光线还有人们好奇的目光：这个以磁铁原理为核心设计的灯具分为上下两个铝制部件，通过磁力相互吸引之后看上去就像是悬浮在空中的 UFO，充满了神秘的感觉。随着两个部件之间的距离变化，安置在黑色部件上的 LED 灯经由上方的镜面扩散开来，而且随时都可以进行调整，允许人们亲自动手与光影产生互动。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-images-wide\"><figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201607191727043exXmIugFkt8Ms6L.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160719172703L0IQmO6vq1wf57zB.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160719172703MxzZQl0FJBpYur2f.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.746667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160719172703aM8vKPnZ9ushodVB.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}